nFromWeb?topicID=341.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Rant against posts in the &quot;things to kill&quot; forums</span><hr size=1> Ok, from time to time I might go through the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> things to kill</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> forums to pass some time. Just in case you have never been through them (* <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> note</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> if you are a long time lurker of the Magician's Tower and have never gone through those sections, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> shame on you</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->*) there are various posts about good places to get experience and/or loot through various levels. However, this is not the problem.<br>
<br>
So, what is the promblem then? There are an awful lot of posts that have something like this in it...<br>
<br>
Summon an earth/air/fire/water pet.<br>
Cast Burnout[2][3][4] on the pet along with a DS.<br>
Equip the pet with...<br>
Pull with...<br>
<br>
stop it!<br>
STOP IT!<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> STOP IT!</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> STOP IT!</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Alright! Enough! By level 12 we <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> KNOW</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to DS our pet and how to cast burnout on it! By level 24 we probably already KNOW which pets best suit our play styles and which pets work better in different situations. Most certainly, this is all very well known by level 50, along with how to pull and fight a mob (if not, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> shame on you</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->). <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> YET</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, these posts continue to happen!<br>
<br>
WHY?!!!!!  They flow through the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> things to kill</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> forums like diarrhea, and there is just no need for it.<br>
<br>
Vilehate Unforgiving<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=izudin>Izudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 120<br> <font color=#333333>(9/30/02 9:43:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=341.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Hehe</span><hr size=1> The posts suggesting hunting spots there should be as detailed as possible. I look there to find ideas where to go. If I havent been in that particular area, I want to be able to start out without having to try (and possibly die) dozens of times...<br>
<br>
Sure in most situations the basic strategies will be absolutely the same...but why not tell if one way to hunt there successfully worked? Why invent the wheel again if you go there?<br>
<br>
Of course I realize the value of exploring and experimenting...but not if I want to go out to get solo exp fast <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Izudin<br>
