<br>
Personally, I have my favorite pets and I tend to use them no matter what.. unless it's a super special case like Lavastorm mobs.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukinelaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kinelaria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 361<br> <font color=#333333>(10/6/02 8:27:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=341.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Hehe</span><hr size=1> Sometimes it's good to know if one pet will do better than another. Like using an air pet against drakes in CS, or an earth pet against shrooms in FG. I also  like to know if a mob is gonna be too tough if I do not have the epic (which I don't currently). Saves alot of time and hassle.<br>
<br>
