<br>
Tell them whether the mobs hit hard and have low HP so they need to burn, or if the mobs are weak and fire pet can mostly solo them.<br>
<br>
Tell them whether it's a fast fight versus a caster and it would be a waste to damage shield your air pet. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naladini>naladini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 561<br> <font color=#333333>(11/4/02 4:35:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=341.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: hehe</span><hr size=1> I seem to remember posting once that pulling (caster) shrooms in Dawnshroud peaks was most effectively done by firing a bolt at max range, then following with a second nuke. <br>
<br>
That would give the mob about 10 seconds of melee against the caster before the pet beat it into retreat. Due to the pulling range, the caster usually won't even get a spell off.<br>
<br>
I'm all for people posting about what spell to pull with. Certain mobs have low MR/FR so pulling with the Mal* line isn't required. Sometimes leading with a DoT or a Nuke can be very effective. I like to read the posts before I start in an area, then do some experimentation on my own and see if I can improve on anything.<br>
<br>
I do agree that posting about BO and providing armor/items for pets gets a bit redundant though.<br>
<br>
My only pet peeve with those forums is the following:<br>
Original Poster: Where Can I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>solo</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> at level X?<br>
Reply: Well first, get a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>partner</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and head to......<br>
<br>
Other than that scenario, those forums have been a great read and provide very nice insight into good xp spots..... <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=381929"> Naladini </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
